The paper deals with the achievable secrecy diversity order of cooperative networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security (cs.CR). The use of relays and interference alignment also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the network and communication sub-categories (cs.NI, cs.SY). Finally, the numerical examples and comparison with existing techniques may also indicate a potential fit for the multimedia sub-category (cs.MM).
